{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_TM1ujDQnoxoXR6u5YUrDqK7u","type":"tool_result","content":"200\tfunctions: []\n201\tcanDelegateTo:\n202\t  - system-research/researcher#deep_research\n203\tprelude: |\n204\t  const researchEnv = request ? await delegate('system-research', 'researcher', 'deep_research', { query: String(request) }) : { ok: false, degraded: true, data: {} };\n205\t---\n206\t\n207\tPackage the domain research for the build step. …\n208\t\n209\tcurrentTask.resolve({ report: (researchEnv && researchEnv.data) ? researchEnv.data : {} });\n210\t````\n211\t\n212\t### `system-architect/synthesize_and_run` — `input: { topic, goal, research }`\n213\t\n214\t**The shipped DAG is eight nodes** (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/01-design.md` … `08-finalize.md`):\n215\t\n216\t```\n217\tdesign (explore, functions: [])\n218\t  → build_field    (forEach: design.fields,    optional, general, [writeKnowledgeIndex, writeKnowledgeOption])\n219\t  → build_function (forEach: design.functions, optional, general, [writeFunctionFile])\n220\t  → write_agent  (general, [writeAgentFile])\n221\t  → write_tasks  (general, [writeTaskFile])\n222\t  → validate     (explore, [validateSpace])\n223\t  → register     (general)\n224\t  → finalize     (goal, explore)\n225\t```\n226\t\n227\tThere is **no research node** — the cited report is handed down in `research` (a JSON *string*) by the caller and seeded straight into `build_field`, so the architect never re-researches (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/index.md:L1-L13`; `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md:L36-L63`). Empty/degraded research is **not** a stop condition — the pipeline runs anyway and the built agent carries the knowledge gaps (`:L66-L69`). `finalize` packages `{ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }`; because `synthesize_and_run` is the action tasklist, its envelope is automatically returned to the caller instead of being manually unpacked in a second model turn.\n228\t\n229\t**Every generated task that loads knowledge carries the grounding rule.** `writeTaskFile` appends it to any instruction containing `loadKnowledge(` that does not already state one (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/functions/writeTaskFile.ts#writeTaskFile`): *state only what the loaded knowledge supports; if it does not answer the query, say so plainly — never infer, guess, or present a conclusion the knowledge does not state.* Without it a fork model asked something its knowledge is **silent** on answers from the nearest note it did load: a built household-insurance agent, asked what its market check concluded, answered from an unrelated car-policy note and told the user a cheaper insurance option had been found — naming their own current insurer — while the saved research row recorded `verified_cheaper_quote_found: false`. The architect's own template writes the rule too (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/05-write_tasks.md:L17-L22`); the writer is the backstop that survives the model paraphrasing it.\n230\t\n231\t### `system-architect/iterate_space` — `input: { spaceKey, feedback }`\n232\t\n233\t```\n234\tload (explore) → diagnose (explore) → edit (general) → reregister (general) → redelegate (goal, general)\n235\t```\n236\tLocate the space, diagnose the feedback, re-write only the affected files with the per-file builders, re-validate, re-register, and hand back the re-run parameters (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/iterate_space/index.md:L1-L11`).\n237\t\n238\t### `system-research/research` — `input: { query }`\n239\t\n240\tOne node, `answer` (goal, explore, `functions: [webSearch, webFetch]`), whose **prelude** does the whole gather (one `webSearch`, one `webFetch` of the top result) so the model only composes (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/tasklists/research/01-answer.md:L1-L16`).\n241\t\n242\t### `system-research/deep_research` — `input: { query }`\n243\t\n244\t```\n245\tscope (explore, [webSearch], prelude: 2 searches)\n246\t  → plan (explore, functions: [])\n247\t  → investigate (forEach: plan.questions, explore, [webSearch, webFetch], prelude: search + fetches)\n248\t  → synthesize (explore, functions: [], prelude: dedup sources + concat findings)\n249\t  → summarize (goal, explore, functions: [])\n250\t```\n251\tEvery deterministic gather/aggregate step lives in a `prelude:`; the model's turns are reserved for synthesis and `resolve` (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/tasklists/deep_research/01-scope.md` … `05-summarize.md`). The goal output is the contract THING and the architect destructure: `{ topic, executive_summary, findings[], conclusion, sources[] }`.\n252\t\n253\t### `system-appbuilder/build_app` — `input: { request }`\n254\t\n255\t```\n256\tdesign (general, functions: [])\n257\t  → create_project (general)\n258\t  → build_table (forEach: design.tables,    optional, general)\n259\t  → build_api   (forEach: design.endpoints, general)\n260\t  → build_page  (forEach: design.pages,     general)\n261\t  → build_hook  (forEach: design.hooks,     optional, general)\n262\t  → finalize (goal, general)\n263\t```\n264\tEach fan-out node writes **exactly one file** with the injected authoring globals (`createProject`/`writeTableSchema`/`writeApi`/`writePage`/`writeHook`) (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/index.md:L1-L12`, `01-design.md` … `07-finalize.md`).\n265\t\n266\t---\n267\t\n268\t## 7. Materialization onto the pod\n269\t\n270\t### 7.1 `materializeRuntime(root)` — on **every** boot path\n271\t\n272\t`materializeRuntime` copies **every** dir from `defaultSystemSpaceDirs()` into `<root>/system/spaces/<name>/`, records each one's shipped content hash in the manifest, and creates the default `user` project skeleton (`<root>/user/{spaces,documents}/`, an empty `instructions.md`, a `project.json`) (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts#materializeRuntime`). Copying zero spaces is a hard misconfiguration and warns loudly — every session would fail to find the `thing` agent (`:L105-L110`).\n273\t\n274\t`<root>` is `LMTHING_ROOT` when set, else `<cwd>/.lmthing` (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/bin.ts#resolveLmthingRoot`). On the compute pod it is the data volume (e.g. `LMTHING_ROOT=/data/.lmthing`).\n275\t\n276\tIt is gated by `runtimeNeedsInit(root)`, which checks for the **sentinel** `<root>/system/spaces/user-thing` — not merely the `system/` dir, because a persistent volume can carry an empty `system/` from an earlier broken materialization and that must be repaired (`sdk/org/libs/cli/src/cli/runtime-init.ts:L51-L67`).\n277\t\n278\tCall sites — this is **not** an `lmthing init`-only step:\n279\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"3ceb5cd9-c606-43d2-a7d6-325d9c85f0e9","timestamp":"2026-07-16T03:46:39.854Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/system-spaces/README.md","content":"functions: []\ncanDelegateTo:\n  - system-research/researcher#deep_research\nprelude: |\n  const researchEnv = request ? await delegate('system-research', 'researcher', 'deep_research', { query: String(request) }) : { ok: false, degraded: true, data: {} };\n---\n\nPackage the domain research for the build step. …\n\ncurrentTask.resolve({ report: (researchEnv && researchEnv.data) ? researchEnv.data : {} });\n````\n\n### `system-architect/synthesize_and_run` — `input: { topic, goal, research }`\n\n**The shipped DAG is eight nodes** (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/01-design.md` … `08-finalize.md`):\n\n```\ndesign (explore, functions: [])\n  → build_field    (forEach: design.fields,    optional, general, [writeKnowledgeIndex, writeKnowledgeOption])\n  → build_functi