{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_NZSpExE5ESt5h653L3VplB9u","type":"tool_result","content":"sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-20-  - system-files/dispatch\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-21-  - user-memory/memory\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:22:  - user-thing/thing#organize_material\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-23-  - user-memory/memory#migrate_to_app_db\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-24-  - \"registered:*\"\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-38-```typescript\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-39-const instr = readProjectFile('instructions.md');\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:40:const docs = listProjectDir('documents');\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-41-```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-42-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-43-Treat `instructions.md` (when present) as standing guidance for this project. When a\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:44:request relates to the user's uploaded material, `listProjectDir('documents')` then\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:45:`readProjectFile('documents/<file>')`. `listProjectDir(dir)`/`readProjectFile(path)` are\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-46-PROJECT-ROOTED (they resolve against the project directory, never a space dir) and are the\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-47-only way to read project files — there is no generic `readFile`/`listDir`/`grep`.\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-370-   ```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-371-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:372:3. **Build a new specialist** — when the user wants a REUSABLE agent/tool/workflow, or the\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-373-   job is a recurring specialized task no existing agent covers (including any \"research X and\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-374-   build a space/agent that …\" request). The `build_specialist` tasklist runs the WHOLE pipeline\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-458-   (\"yes please\", \"go on then\", \"sure\"). A bare yes to YOUR OWN offer is CONSENT: when the offer\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-459-   was to organize supplied material, emit **exactly one statement**. It starts the organizer and\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:460:   composes the closing reply from its envelope inline — values do not persist into a later statement:\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-461-   ```typescript\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:462:   await tasklist('organize_material', {\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-463-     request: '<what you offered>',\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-464-     sourceSummary: '<the short attachment summary>',\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-515-   // Read app yourself, then tell them what they can now open. Never dump it.\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-516-   ```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:517:   **Before you tell them it is ready, CHECK that it is.** A builder that comes back cheerful is not\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-518-   proof of anything — the only proof is the deliverable. So after the build, LOOK at what actually\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:519:   landed (`listProjectDir`) and ask the question the user will ask: *can they open it?* A project\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-520-   with tables and no page is not an app they can open — it is data in a drawer, and announcing it as\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-521-   live is a lie they will discover the moment they tap the link. If a piece is missing, finish it\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-704-```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-705-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:706:`listProjectDir('api')` shows which endpoints exist; the typed names are in your ambient types. Two\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-707-numbers for the same question is a bug the user WILL notice — and the one on their screen is the one\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-708-they trust. So when a figure is already computed by the app, the app is the source of truth: reading\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-40-| **`system-global`** | *(none — function-only)* | — | The **universally injected toolkit**: 8 functions, in scope in every agent, fork and delegate (§3). |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-41-| **`system-engineer`** | `engineer` | *(none — model-driven)* | Drafts/fixes/**verifies** code in a private **scratch sandbox** — `createScratch()` first, then a jailed `readFile`/`writeFile`/`editFile`/`listDir`/`glob`/`grep` + `execShell` (absolute/`..` paths rejected), with `fork({role:'explore'\\|'plan'})` for heavy investigation (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-engineer/agents/engineer/instruct.md:L28-L45`). It does **not** read or write the live project; it **returns** the finished code to its caller via `currentTask.resolve({ ok, kind:'projectFunction'\\|'code', code, suggestedName?, notes? })`, and the caller persists it with a typed writer (`:L73-L98`). Holds `fs:scratch` only — no `writeProjectFunction`. |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:42:| **`system-architect`** | `architect` | `synthesize_and_run` *(default)*, `iterate_space` | The **meta-agent that builds other agents**. Each action starts its tasklist in one statement; the action runtime returns that tasklist envelope to its caller, while the real work happens inside the tasklists (§6). Owns 13 scoped builder functions: `writeAgentFile`, `writeTaskFile`, `writeKnowledgeIndex`, `writeKnowledgeOption`, `writeFunctionFile`, `writeComponentFile`, `writeEventFile`, `writeHookFile`, `writeManifest`, `readSpaceFile`, `listSpaceDir`, `validateSpace`, `listScaffoldedSpaces` (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md:L5-L18`). Knowledge: `space_format/frontmatter`. **Every agent it synthesizes is granted `knowledge:write` and gets a standing `research_and_store` tasklist** (`writeAgentFile`/`writeTaskFile` now emit `capabilities:`), so a question outside its static knowledge is researched and SAVED into its own knowledge instead of guessed (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/05-write_tasks.md`). |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-43-| **`system-research`** | `researcher` | `research` *(default)*, `deep_research` | Web research. `research` = one search + one fetch + a concise sourced answer; `deep_research` = a 5-stage cited-report pipeline (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-research/agents/researcher/instruct.md:L6-L16`). Ships **no functions of its own** — its tasks reach the web through `system-global`'s `webSearch`/`webFetch`, allow-listed per task. |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-44-| **`system-appbuilder`** | `app-architect` | `build_app` *(default)* | Builds a whole application — **the store-catalog template path**. Runs the `build_app` tasklist and reports; may delegate one slice to a specialist (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/agents/app-architect/instruct.md:L29-L54`). |\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-123-| 1 | **Answer directly** | general knowledge, conversation, reasoning | `display(...)`, no delegation — the default for most messages (`:L125-L127`) |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-124-| 2 | **Research the web** | current/external facts **as the final answer** | `delegate('system-research','researcher','research',{query})`; `deep_research` **only on explicit request** (\"deep\"/\"thorough\"/\"comprehensive\"/report) — it costs ~10× more (`:L129-L158`) |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:125:| 3 | **Build a new specialist** | the user wants a **reusable agent/tool/workflow** | two turns: `await tasklist('build_specialist',{request})`, then `delegate(b.data.spaceKey, b.data.agentSlug, b.data.actionId, …)` guarded on `b.ok && b.data.ok` (`:L160-L180`). **When the material is already provided** (attached file / in-conversation), it must NOT run `build_specialist` — it delegates straight to `architect#synthesize_and_run` with the content seeded as `context.research` (a JSON string), which skips the research fork entirely (`:L182-L205`) |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-126-| 4a | **App IN this project** (the DEFAULT app target) | \"turn this into an app\", \"an app for my trip/notes/data\", anything built on data already in this project | `delegate('system-appbuilder','automator',{query, attachmentIds})` — it first derives one specialist per distinct independently owned scope, then authors tables (seeding rows), API handlers, pages and hooks **directly into the live project**, served at `/app/<project>/` (`:L228-L251`) |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-127-| 4a′ | **A CHANGED FACT about data already in the app** | \"I renewed the car insurance, the new policy number is AX-7741-2\", \"the rent went up to €900\", \"mark that invoice paid\" | THING now holds `db:write`, so a change to an EXISTING table it does **itself** — `db.query` to find the row, then `db.update` (or via the `write_fact`/`retract_fact` tasklists) — the automator is only for a change that needs a NEW table/page (`db:schema`/`pages:write`, which THING lacks). **Not** the domain space: `household-insurance-admin` and friends READ their knowledge and REPLY (their `answer` tasklist cannot write the db), so an update routed there yields a fluent confirmation and changes nothing. Route on the **intent, not the words** — the Greek twin of the sentence takes the same path (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:L506-L523`) |\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-174-## 6. The shipped tasklists (the host-driven DAGs)\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-175-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:176:Six tasklists ship across four spaces. The tasklist mechanics (`role`, `functions`, `forEach`, `prelude`, `dependsOn`, `goal`, the `{ok, degraded, data}` envelope) are documented in [`../format/space/tasklists/README.md`](../format/space/tasklists/README.md) and [`../runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md`](../runtime/fork-and-tasklists.md) — here is what each shipped DAG actually is.\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-177-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:178:### `user-thing/organize_material` — `input: { request, sourceSummary, attachmentIds, specialistFacts }`\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-179-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:180:For the explicit agreement after THING offers to organize supplied material, this DAG first reads every supplied document and inventories its stable independently-owned scopes; the partition follows the material's primary operational axis (bounded stages in a sequence, independently run operations in parallel), not storage categories such as costs, contacts, documents, or media. It then runs `build_specialist` as a `forEach` over `inventory.scopes` and, once every specialist has finished, delegates the complete source plus attachment IDs to the live-project automator. THING invokes this workflow exactly once and consumes its envelope inline with its closing reply: statement-local values cannot safely drive a later continuation. Facts, photographs, memories, shared overviews, and cross-cutting groupings stay with their owning scope or app data: they do not become their own specialist. An uninterrupted operational stage can combine its subparts, but separate locations or stages remain separate (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:L457-L480`, `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/organize_material/index.md:L1-L11`, `01-inventory.md:L1-L29`, `02-build_specialist.md:L1-L22`, `03-build_app.md:L1-L23`).\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-181-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-182-### `user-thing/build_specialist` — `input: { request }`\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-187-```\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-188-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:189:The `research` node is `optional: true` and its **prelude** performs the delegation, so the model's only job is to package the envelope; the `build` node **always runs** (a skipped dependency is satisfied) and returns the built agent's run coordinates `{ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }` (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/tasklists/build_specialist/index.md:L1-L14`, `01-research.md:L1-L25`, `02-build.md`). The whole research node, verbatim:\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-190-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-191-````markdown\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-225-```\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-226-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md:227:There is **no research node** — the cited report is handed down in `research` (a JSON *string*) by the caller and seeded straight into `build_field`, so the architect never re-researches (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/index.md:L1-L13`; `sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/agents/architect/instruct.md:L36-L63`). Empty/degraded research is **not** a stop condition — the pipeline runs anyway and the built agent carries the knowledge gaps (`:L66-L69`). `finalize` packages `{ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }`; because `synthesize_and_run` is the action tasklist, its envelope is automatically returned to the caller instead of being manually unpacked in a second model turn.\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-228-\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-229-**Every generated task that loads knowledge carries the grounding rule.** `writeTaskFile` appends it to any instruction containing `loadKnowledge(` that does not already state one (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/functions/writeTaskFile.ts#writeTaskFile`): *state only what the loaded knowledge supports; if it does not answer the query, say so plainly — never infer, guess, or present a conclusion the knowledge does not state.* Without it a fork model asked something its knowledge is **silent** on answers from the nearest note it did load: a built household-insurance agent, asked what its market check concluded, answered from an unrelated car-policy note and told the user a cheaper insurance option had been found — naming their own current insurer — while the saved research row recorded `verified_cheaper_quote_found: false`. The architect's own template writes the rule too (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/05-write_tasks.md:L17-L22`); the writer is the backstop that survives the model paraphrasing it.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"06e86f29-a36b-49e0-8a27-de5152908f7d","timestamp":"2026-07-16T03:46:42.386Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-20-  - system-files/dispatch\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-21-  - user-memory/memory\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:22:  - user-thing/thing#organize_material\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-23-  - user-memory/memory#migrate_to_app_db\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-24-  - \"registered:*\"\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-38-```typescript\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-39-const instr = readProjectFile('instructions.md');\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:40:const docs = listProjectDir('documents');\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-41-```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-42-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-43-Treat `instructions.md` (when present) as standing guidance for this project. When a\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:44:request relates to the user's uploaded material, `listProjectDir('documents')` then\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:45:`readProjectFile('documents/<file>')`. `listProjectDir(dir)`/`readProjectFile(path)` are\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-46-PROJECT-ROOTED (they resolve against the project directory, never a space dir) and are the\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-47-only way to read project files — there is no generic `readFile`/`listDir`/`grep`.\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-370-   ```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-371-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:372:3. **Build a new specialist** — when the user wants a REUSABLE agent/tool/workflow, or the\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-373-   job is a recurring specialized task no existing agent covers (including any \"research X and\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-374-   build a space/agent that …\" request). The `build_specialist` tasklist runs the WHOLE pipeline\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-458-   (\"yes please\", \"go on then\", \"sure\"). A bare yes to YOUR OWN offer is CONSENT: when the offer\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-459-   was to organize supplied material, emit **exactly one statement**. It starts the organizer and\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:460:   composes the closing reply from its envelope inline — values do not persist into a later statement:\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-461-   ```typescript\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:462:   await tasklist('organize_material', {\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-463-     request: '<what you offered>',\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-464-     sourceSummary: '<the short attachment summary>',\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-515-   // Read app yourself, then tell them what they can now open. Never dump it.\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-516-   ```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:517:   **Before you tell them it is ready, CHECK that it is.** A builder that comes back cheerful is not\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-518-   proof of anything — the only proof is the deliverable. So after the build, LOOK at what actually\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:519:   landed (`listProjectDir`) and ask the question the user will ask: *can they open it?* A project\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-520-   with tables and no page is not an app they can open — it is data in a drawer, and announcing it as\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-521-   live is a lie they will discover the moment they tap the link. If a piece is missing, finish it\n--\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-704-```\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-705-\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:706:`listProjectDir('api')` shows which endpoints exist; the typed names are in your ambient types. Two\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-707-numbers for the same question is a bug the user WILL notice — and the one on their screen is the one\nsdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md-708-they trust. So when a figure is already computed by the app, the app is the source of truth: reading\n--\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-40-| **`system-global`** | *(none — function-only)* | — | The **universally injected toolkit**: 8 functions, in scope in every agent, fork and delegate (§3). |\norg/docs/system-spaces/README.md-41-| **`system-engineer`** | `engineer` | *(none — model-driven)* | Drafts/fixes/**verifies** code in a private **scratch sandbox** — `createScratch()` first, then a jailed `readFile`/`writeFile`/`editFile`/`listDir`/`glob`/`grep` + `execShell` (absolute/`..` paths rejected), with `fork({role:'explore'\\|'plan'})` for heavy investigation (`sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-engineer/agents/engineer/instruct.md:L28-L45`). It does **not** read or write the live project; it **returns** the finished code to its caller via `currentTask.resolve({ ok, kind:'projectFunction'\\|'code', code, suggestedName?, notes? })`, and the caller persists it with a typed writer (`:L73-L98`). Holds `f