{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_2b4kFTQFRe6n9Fv6rvQlCEcA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_app\n3\toutput:\n4\t  ok: boolean\n5\t  detail: string\n6\tdependsOn: [build_specialist]\n7\tgoal: true\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\tcanDelegateTo:\n11\t  - system-appbuilder/automator\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\tBuild the live-project app after every inventoried specialist has finished. `request`,\n15\t`sourceSummary`, `attachmentIds`, `specialistFacts`, and `build_specialist` are in scope. Pass every\n16\tattachment id to the automator so it reads all source files itself; include `specialistFacts` because\n17\timage and audio facts cannot be re-read. Mention any failed specialist build in the request, but\n18\tstill build the app from the complete supplied source. Emit exactly one self-contained statement that\n19\tdelegates and resolves without relying on a later statement or cross-turn variable:\n20\t\n21\tcurrentTask.resolve(await delegate('system-appbuilder', 'automator', { query: String(request) + '\\n\\nSource summary:\\n' + String(sourceSummary) + '\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\n' + String(specialistFacts) + '\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n' + JSON.stringify(build_specialist), attachmentIds: attachmentIds as string[] }).then((app) => ({ ok: !!(app && app.ok === true), detail: JSON.stringify((app && app.data) ? app.data : {}) })));"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_XOUkCCKPWXZ8vWn7RxhEWgPz","session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"dd88fdff-0787-476d-8ca4-533137bf32ab","timestamp":"2026-07-16T03:56:12.767Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace automator build failure"}
