{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_vb3XxFLGUSquHceFwj8L2TCx","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: design\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  title: string\n6\t  tables: array\n7\t  pages: array\n8\t  endpoints: array\n9\t  hooks: array\n10\tdependsOn: []\n11\trole: general\n12\tfunctions: []\n13\t---\n14\t\n15\tDesign the whole app from `request`. This is the THINKING step: reason from the request into a\n16\tconcrete build plan, then resolve it. You have no file tools here — just produce the plan object.\n17\t\n18\tSubstitute REAL values for every `<…>` below (never leave a placeholder in the resolved values).\n19\tDerive a short lowercase-slug `appId` from the request (letters/digits/hyphen, starts with a\n20\tletter). Each endpoint `route` MUST encode its HTTP method last, e.g. `items-list/GET` or\n21\t`items-create/POST`. Each page `route` is `index` (the app root) or a path like `items/[id]`.\n22\t\n23\tconst appId = \"<lowercase-slug derived from the request, e.g. habit-tracker>\";\n24\tconst title = \"<human-readable app title>\";\n25\t// Each table: { name, schema } where schema = { title, description, columns:{...}, relations? }.\n26\t// Every column and relation needs a description; exactly one primaryKey column (uuid).\n27\tconst tables = [\n28\t  { name: \"<table_slug>\", schema: { title: \"<Title>\", description: \"<what it stores>\", columns: { id: { type: \"string\", description: \"unique id\", primaryKey: true, generated: \"uuid\" } } } }\n29\t];\n30\t// Each endpoint: { route: \"<name>/<METHOD>\", purpose }. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\n31\tconst endpoints = [\n32\t  { route: \"<name>/GET\", purpose: \"<what this endpoint returns or does>\" }\n33\t];\n34\t// Each page: { route, purpose }. Use \"index\" for the root page.\n35\tconst pages = [\n36\t  { route: \"index\", purpose: \"<what the root page shows>\" }\n37\t];\n38\t// Each hook (often none): { slug, purpose }. Cron or database-triggered automation.\n39\tconst hooks = [];\n40\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId, title, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks });\n41\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"4266be8c-f48e-4143-8886-a8a17a3f5182","timestamp":"2026-07-16T03:57:44.593Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/01-design.md","content":"---\nid: design\noutput:\n  appId: string\n  title: string\n  tables: array\n  pages: array\n  endpoints: array\n  hooks: array\ndependsOn: []\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nDesign the whole app from `request`. This is the THINKING step: reason from the request into a\nconcrete build plan, then resolve it. You have no file tools here — just produce the plan object.\n\nSubstitute REAL values for every `<…>` below (never leave a placeholder in the resolved values).\nDerive a short lowercase-slug `appId` from the request (letters/digits/hyphen, starts with a\nletter). Each endpoint `route` MUST encode its HTTP method last, e.g. `items-list/GET` or\n`items-create/POST`. Each page `route` is `index` (the app root) or a path like `items/[id]`.\n\nconst appId = \"<lowercase-slug derived from the request, e.g. habit-tracker>\";\nconst title = \"<human-readable app title>\";\n// Each table: { name, schema } where schema = { title, description, columns:{...}, relations? }.\n// Every column and relation needs a description; exactly one primaryKey column (uuid).\nconst tables = [\n  { name: \"<table_slug>\", schema: { title: \"<Title>\", description: \"<what it stores>\", columns: { id: { type: \"string\", description: \"unique id\", primaryKey: true, generated: \"uuid\" } } } }\n];\n// Each endpoint: { route: \"<name>/<METHOD>\", purpose }. Methods: GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE.\nconst endpoints = [\n  { route: \"<name>/GET\", purpose: \"<what this endpoint returns or does>\" }\n];\n// Each page: { route, purpose }. Use \"index\" for the root page.\nconst pages = [\n  { route: \"index\", purpose: \"<what the root page shows>\" }\n];\n// Each hook (often none): { slug, purpose }. Cron or database-triggered automation.\nconst hooks = [];\ncurrentTask.resolve({ appId, title, tables, pages, endpoints, hooks });\n","numLines":41,"startLine":1,"totalLines":41}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_lVDSGtzJ4SLMZzKeTdd2O7PS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: create_project\n3\toutput:\n4\t  appId: string\n5\t  root: string\n6\t  ok: boolean\n7\tdependsOn: [design]\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tCreate the project that every later step writes into. Call `createProject` with the designed\n13\t`appId` and title, then resolve. `createProject` selects the new project as the current authoring\n14\ttarget, so the downstream table/api/page/hook writers land inside it. Emit:\n15\t\n16\tconst c = createProject(design.appId, { title: design.title });\n17\t// c = { ok, appId?, root?, error? }. If c.ok is false, the appId likely collides — read c.error.\n18\tcurrentTask.resolve({ appId: c.ok ? (c.appId ?? design.appId) : design.appId, root: c.root ?? \"\", ok: c.ok });\n19\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"8fd5efa8-e4c3-469c-a0ce-9eeb6e5fb694","timestamp":"2026-07-16T03:57:44.593Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/02-create_project.md","content":"---\nid: create_project\noutput:\n  appId: string\n  root: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [design]\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nCreate the project that every later step writes into. Call `createProject` with the designed\n`appId` and title, then resolve. `createProject` selects the new project as the current authoring\ntarget, so the downstream table/api/page/hook writers land inside it. Emit:\n\nconst c = createProject(design.appId, { title: design.title });\n// c = { ok, appId?, root?, error? }. If c.ok is false, the appId likely collides — read c.error.\ncurrentTask.resolve({ appId: c.ok ? (c.appId ?? design.appId) : design.appId, root: c.root ?? \"\", ok: c.ok });\n","numLines":19,"startLine":1,"totalLines":19}}}
