{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_XkHkDCtkGwKmt8q2In3i5LSt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_hook\n3\toutput:\n4\t  slug: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [design, build_table]\n7\tforEach: design.hooks\n8\toptional: true\n9\trole: general\n10\tfunctions: []\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\tWrite ONE automation hook into the project's `hooks/`. Your hook is in `item` = { slug, purpose }.\n14\tWrite the FULL `.ts` source inline. There is NO `{ type: 'database' }` hook anymore — a project-db\n15\twrite is delivered as the EVENT `project/db.<table>.<event>` (`event` ∈ `insert`|`update`|`remove`),\n16\twhose emitted payload IS the written row. So a hook default-exports `{ type: 'event' | 'cron', … }`:\n17\t\n18\t- **Event hook** (react to a db write, or to an installed space's event) — subscribe to ONE\n19\t  source-qualified address and either run a code `handler` (the handler IS the filter — cheap, no\n20\t  LLM) or `trigger` an agent. A code handler receives `ctx = { input, db, delegate, callConnection,\n21\t  tasklist }` — `input` is the event payload (the row for a `project/db.*` event); `ctx.db` is the\n22\t  project's async data API (`await ctx.db.insert(table, row)` / `query` / `update` / `remove`).\n23\t  There is no `ctx.project.db` and no `ctx.publishEvent` — use `ctx.db` only.\n24\t- **Cron hook** — `{ type: 'cron', every: '1d' | daily: 'HH:MM', trigger: '<space>/<agent>#<action>' }`.\n25\t\n26\tGround `table` in a table you designed and any `trigger` in a REAL agent action (never a self-\n27\ttrigger back into `app-architect#build_app`). Emit ONE of these shapes for your `item`:\n28\t\n29\t```typescript\n30\tconst h = item;\n31\tconst table = design.tables[0] ? design.tables[0].name : 'items';\n32\t// Code-handler event hook: enrich each freshly inserted row in plain code (no LLM).\n33\tconst src = [\n34\t  \"export default {\",\n35\t  \"  type: 'event',\",\n36\t  \"  on: { event: 'project/db.\" + table + \".insert' },\",\n37\t  \"  handler: async ({ input, db }) => {\",\n38\t  \"    const row = input;\",\n39\t  \"    if (!row || !row.id) return;\",\n40\t  \"    // ... derive fields and persist with ctx.db; e.g.:\",\n41\t  \"    // await db.update('\" + table + \"', { where: { id: row.id }, set: { seen: true } });\",\n42\t  \"  },\",\n43\t  \"};\",\n44\t].join(\"\\n\");\n45\tconst w = writeHook(h.slug, src);\n46\t// w = { ok, error? }. Rewrite and retry if w.ok is false.\n47\tcurrentTask.resolve({ slug: h.slug, ok: w.ok });\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\tTo hand the event to an agent instead of writing code, replace `handler` with\n51\t`trigger: '<space>/<agent>#<action>'` (mutually exclusive with `handler`). Prefer a code `handler`\n52\twhenever the reaction is a simple filter/relay — no agent, no LLM cost.\n53\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"625ee3e5-57b1-42a3-9cc2-762259deb6f8","uuid":"b19419bc-bee2-4590-85f2-7eafda8c187e","timestamp":"2026-07-16T04:10:14.307Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_app/06-build_hook.md","content":"---\nid: build_hook\noutput:\n  slug: string\n  ok: boolean\ndependsOn: [design, build_table]\nforEach: design.hooks\noptional: true\nrole: general\nfunctions: []\n---\n\nWrite ONE automation hook into the project's `hooks/`. Your hook is in `item` = { slug, purpose }.\nWrite the FULL `.ts` source inline. There is NO `{ type: 'database' }` hook anymore — a project-db\nwrite is delivered as the EVENT `project/db.<table>.<event>` (`event` ∈ `insert`|`update`|`remove`),\nwhose emitted payload IS the written row. So a hook default-exports `{ type: 'event' | 'cron', … }`:\n\n- **Event hook** (react to a db write, or to an installed space's event) — subscribe to ONE\n  source-qualified address and either run a code `handler` (the handler IS the filter — cheap, no\n  LLM) or `trigger` an agent. A code handler receives `ctx = { input, db, delegate, callConnection,\n  tasklist }` — `input` is the event payload (the row for a `project/db.*` event); `ctx.db` is the\n  project's async data API (`await ctx.db.insert(table, row)` / `query` / `update` / `remove`).\n  There is no `ctx.project.db` and no `ctx.publishEvent` — use `ctx.db` only.\n- **Cron hook** — `{ type: 'cron', every: '1d' | daily: 'HH:MM', trigger: '<space>/<agent>#<action>' }`.\n\nGround `table` in a table you designed and any `trigger` in a REAL agent action (never a self-\ntrigger back into `app-architect#build_app`). Emit ONE of these shapes for your `item`:\n\n```typescript\nconst h = item;\nconst table = design.tables[0] ? design.tables[0].name : 'items';\n// Code-handler event hook: enrich each freshly inserted row in plain code (no LLM).\nconst src = [\n  \"export default {\",\n  \"  type: 'event',\",\n  \"  on: { event: 'project/db.\" + table + \".insert' },\",\n  \"  handler: async ({ input, db }) => {\",\n  \"    const row = input;\",\n  \"    if (!row || !row.id) return;\",\n  \"    // ... derive fields and persist with ctx.db; e.g.:\",\n  \"    // await db.update('\" + table + \"', { where: { id: row.id }, set: { seen: true } });\",\n  \"  },\",\n  \"};\",\n].join(\"\\n\");\nconst w = writeHook(h.slug, src);\n// w = { ok, error? }. Rewrite and retry if w.ok is false.\ncurrentTask.resolve({ slug: h.slug, ok: w.ok });\n```\n\nTo hand the event to an agent instead of writing code, replace `handler` with\n`trigger: '<space>/<agent>#<action>'` (mutually exclusive with `handler`). Prefer a code `handler`\nwhenever the reaction is a simple filter/relay — no agent, no LLM cost.\n","numLines":53,"startLine":1,"totalLines":53}}}
