u…\"\n134\t        }\n135\t      ],\n136\t      \"errors\": [\n137\t        {\n138\t          \"type\": \"typecheck_error\",\n139\t          \"message\": \"Property 'find' does not exist on type '{ ok: boolean; entries: string[]; error?: string | undefined; }'.\",\n140\t          \"statement\": \"// They said yes to the offer — now I run the organizer tasklist with all the material.\\n// The organizer owns the complete build: inventories independently-owned scopes, builds every grounded specialist,\\n// then hands the complete source to the live-project builder. I pass ALL attachment ids plus the voice-memo facts\\n// (which only I could transcribe — the builder cannot hear audio) and the image summary (builder cannot see images).\\n\\nawait tasklist('organize_material', {\\n  request: 'Organize the user\\\\'s entire Tanzania trip into a single app they can open on their phone. They have scattered material: notes with flight details and route, a cost spreadsheet, a park-fee PDF, a Stone Town photo, and a voice memo from Ngorongoro crater. Build per-topic specialist spaces for the distinct parts (flights, safari/Ngorongoro, Zanzibar/Stone Town, costs), then build the live-project app with tables seeded from all provided data, pages for each section, and the photo included.',\\n  sourceSummary: 'Three files: tanzaniamemories.md (full trip notes with confirmed flights, route, contacts), trip-costs.xlsx (cost spreadsheet), ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf (official park fees). One image: stone-town-zanzibar.jpg (bright white building with dark wooden balconies, Zanzibar light). One voice memo: Ngorongoro crater day — guide named Emmanuel, bought two beaded bracelets for Athina Mari from a Maasai lady at the rim for ~TZS 35,000 (roughly $20-25), Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~TZS 5,000 cash at the gate separate from park fees, need to ask Richard about it before safari balance payment.',\\n  attachmentIds: ['0a445eb7-663d-4e2a-a097-25a936f7c6dd', '65c